          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "QMPH"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The method of the positron annihilation in",
                " flight was used to produce quasimonoenergetic photons",
                " of variable energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". 4PI liquid scintillation tank (NE233) loaded",
                " with 0.3% gadolinium was used. It had a high",
                " efficiency (30-90%), which was independent of",
                " incident neutrons energy. the detector was surrounded",
                " by a 10 cm paraffin shield.",
                "Three type of monitors were used:",
                " - Faraday cup for current measurements and for center",
                "   ring of a beam;",
                " - profile and position monitor for the detection of",
                "   the beam size and position in front;",
                " - indication monitor for non-intercepting current",
                "   monitoring in front of annihilation target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "N"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The total photoneutron cross sections for C-12 and O-1",
                " nuclei were measured as difference between yields",
                " measured for positron and electron beams."
              ]
            }
          ],
